# Accepted, documented vulnerability exceptions for the Trivy CI gate.
# The non-blocking "Trivy report" step does NOT use this file, so these still
# show up in CI logs for visibility.

# CVE-2025-68121 — Go stdlib crypto/tls: incorrect certificate validation during
# TLS session resumption. Present in the upstream dnsx/naabu Go binaries (compiled
# with Go < 1.24.13). We already pin the latest available releases (dnsx 1.2.3,
# naabu 2.6.1); no fixed tool release exists yet. Out of our control until
# ProjectDiscovery rebuilds with patched Go — revisit and bump the pins then.
CVE-2025-68121
